<div class="bg-white text-gray-900">
  <section class="relative isolate overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-sky-50 via-white to-indigo-50">
    <div class="mx-auto flex max-w-6xl flex-col gap-6 px-4 py-16 sm:py-20">
      <p class="inline-flex w-fit items-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-white/70 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-sky-700 ring-1 ring-sky-200">
        Guide
      </p>
      <div class="max-w-3xl space-y-4">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold leading-tight text-gray-900 sm:text-5xl">
          How to Use MuDG
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">
          Explore arguments with friends or students, build graphs together, and keep every thread of the conversation linked to evidence.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-10 sm:py-14 space-y-12">
    <div class="grid gap-6 rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm sm:grid-cols-2 sm:p-8">
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-sky-50 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-sky-700 ring-1 ring-sky-200">
          Step 1
        </div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Start a conversation</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          Pick a topic, invite collaborators, and ask MuDG to map the ideas. Every reply becomes part of the shared graph so you can reference it later.
          <br /><br /> If you’re not sure where to start, try the
          <a href="/inspiration" class="font-medium text-sky-700 underline hover:text-sky-800">
            Inspire me
          </a>
          page for ideas.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-r from-indigo-50 to-sky-50 p-6 ring-1 ring-indigo-100">
        <p class="text-base font-medium text-gray-800">Quick tips</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-4 text-gray-700">
          <li>Use follow-up questions to expand the graph with evidence and counter-points.</li>
          <li>Use actions to quickly create chains of thought</li>
          <li>Save snapshots when you reach agreement to revisit the reasoning later.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div
      class="group grid gap-6 rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm sm:p-8"
      phx-hook="InterfaceHighlight"
      data-interface-highlight-initial=""
      id="interface-highlight"
    >
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-indigo-50 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-indigo-700 ring-1 ring-indigo-200">
          Step 2
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Get comfortable with the interface</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          Hover the labels to see which part of the workspace they control.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="relative">
        <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-gray-900/5 shadow-md">
          <img
            src="/images/graph_live.webp"
            alt="MuDG interface showing responses, graph visualisation, action tools, and admin panel"
            class="block w-full h-auto"
          />
          <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0">
            <div
              class="absolute rounded-lg ring-4 ring-yellow-300 bg-yellow-300/10 shadow-[0_0_0_6px_rgba(253,224,71,0.45)] transition-opacity duration-200 opacity-0 group-data-[interface-highlight-active=responses]:opacity-100"
              aria-hidden="true"
              style="left: 0.8%; top: 0.8%; width: 37.586%; height: 98.4%;"
            >
            </div>
            <div
              class="absolute rounded-lg ring-4 ring-yellow-300 bg-yellow-300/10 shadow-[0_0_0_6px_rgba(253,224,71,0.45)] transition-opacity duration-200 opacity-0 group-data-[interface-highlight-active=graph]:opacity-100"
              aria-hidden="true"
              style="left: 39.986%; top: 0.8%; width: 29.225%; height: 76.854%;"
            >
            </div>
            <div
              class="absolute rounded-lg ring-4 ring-yellow-300 bg-yellow-300/10 shadow-[0_0_0_6px_rgba(253,224,71,0.45)] transition-opacity duration-200 opacity-0 group-data-[interface-highlight-active=tools]:opacity-100"
              aria-hidden="true"
              style="left: 43.172%; top: 85.461%; width: 33.666%; height: 13.622%;"
            >
            </div>
            <div
              class="absolute rounded-lg ring-4 ring-yellow-300 bg-yellow-300/10 shadow-[0_0_0_6px_rgba(253,224,71,0.45)] transition-opacity duration-200 opacity-0 group-data-[interface-highlight-active=admin]:opacity-100"
              aria-hidden="true"
              style="left: 80.8%; top: 0.8%; width: 18.254%; height: 98.166%;"
            >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div
          class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50/60 p-3 transition-colors hover:border-indigo-200 hover:bg-indigo-50/50"
          data-interface-highlight-trigger="responses"
        >
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-700">Responses</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            The text content.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50/60 p-3 transition-colors hover:border-sky-200 hover:bg-sky-50/60"
          data-interface-highlight-trigger="graph"
        >
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-sky-700">Visualisation</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            An interactive diagram of ideas and their relationships.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50/60 p-3 transition-colors hover:border-amber-200 hover:bg-amber-50/60"
          data-interface-highlight-trigger="tools"
        >
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-700">Action tools</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            Controls for common actions: Pros / Cons, exploring related ideas, combining concepts, Translate and Deep Dive.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50/60 p-3 transition-colors hover:border-emerald-200 hover:bg-emerald-50/60"
          data-interface-highlight-trigger="admin"
        >
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-emerald-700">Admin panel</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            Search, set LLM personality, control who has access, create groups, see notes others have written, share the graph, and download the content.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-6 rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm sm:grid-cols-3 sm:p-8">
      <div class="sm:col-span-2 space-y-3">
        <p class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-emerald-700 ring-1 ring-emerald-200">
          Teacher's Guide
        </p>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
          Create, lock, and share a classroom graph
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          Use MuDG to build a structured “map” of a topic, then lock it so students explore the learning path you designed.
          Share a URL so everyone can join the same graph.
        </p>
        <ol class="list-decimal space-y-2 pl-5 text-gray-700">
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Create a graph:</span>
            start an exploration and build out the key nodes, claims, and sources for your topic.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Lock it in the Admin panel:</span>
            use the lock feature to prevent unintended edits while students navigate and discuss.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Share the URL:</span>
            send the link to students so they can follow the graph, ask questions, and add notes where allowed.
          </li>
        </ol>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          You can also have groups build competing graphs and then merge the best claims into a shared synthesis.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-br from-emerald-50 to-white p-5 ring-1 ring-emerald-100">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-emerald-800">Share the guide</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
          Copy this page URL and paste it into your lesson plan, LMS, or class chat.
        </p>
        <button
          type="button"
          class="mt-4 inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-emerald-600 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm transition hover:bg-emerald-700"
          onclick="
            (async () => {
              const btn = this;
              const original = btn.dataset.originalText || btn.textContent.trim();
              btn.dataset.originalText = original;

              const url = window.location.href;

              try {
                if (navigator.clipboard && navigator.clipboard.writeText) {
                  await navigator.clipboard.writeText(url);
                } else {
                  const ta = document.createElement('textarea');
                  ta.value = url;
                  ta.setAttribute('readonly', 'true');
                  ta.style.position = 'fixed';
                  ta.style.top = '-9999px';
                  ta.style.left = '-9999px';
                  document.body.appendChild(ta);
                  ta.select();
                  document.execCommand('copy');
                  document.body.removeChild(ta);
                }

                btn.textContent = 'Copied!';
              } catch (_e) {
                btn.textContent = 'Copy failed';
              }

              window.clearTimeout(btn._copyResetTimer);
              btn._copyResetTimer = window.setTimeout(() => {
                btn.textContent = original;
              }, 1600);
            })();
          "
        >
          Copy lesson link
        </button>
        <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-emerald-900/70">
          Clicking will copy the current page URL to your clipboard.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

